<title>USA: Chesapeake Corp to buy back up to 2 mln shrs.</title>
<headline>Chesapeake Corp to buy back up to 2 mln shrs.</headline>
<dateline>RICHMOND, Va. 1997-08-13</dateline>
<text>
<p>Chesapeake Corp said Wednesday its board authorized the repurchase of up to two million shares of its common stock in open market purchases and negotiated transactions.</p>
<p>The company said this amounts to about 8 percent of its currently outstanding shares.</p>
<p>The company said it is authorized to make the purchase from time to time over the next year.</p>
<p>Chesapeake said it expects to use a portion of the proceeds from the May sale of its West Point, Va. kraft products mill and associated assets to fund any share repurchases.</p>
